    SupportPage --> HelpDeskDashboard: Click Help Desk Tab
    SupportPage --> SupportTickets: Click Support Tickets Tab
    SupportPage --> KnowledgeBase: Click Knowledge Base Tab
    SupportPage --> SupportReports: Click Reports Tab
    SupportPage --> SupportSettings: Click Settings Tab
    
    SupportPage --> CreateTicket: Click Create New Ticket
    SupportTickets --> TicketDetails: Click on Ticket
    SupportTickets --> ExportData: Click Export Data
    
    TicketDetails --> ReplyToTicket: Click Reply
    TicketDetails --> ReassignTicket: Click Reassign
    TicketDetails --> SupportTickets: Click Back
    
    KnowledgeBase --> CreateArticle: Click Create Article
    
    ReplyToTicket --> TicketDetails: After Send/Cancel
    ReassignTicket --> TicketDetails: After Confirm/Cancel
    CreateTicket --> SupportTickets: After Create/Cancel
    CreateArticle --> KnowledgeBase: After Publish/Cancel
    ExportData --> SupportTickets: After Generate/Cancel
    
    note right of TicketDetails
        Ticket Details displays comprehensive 
        information about a specific support ticket,
        including customer information, response
        history, and available actions.
    end note
    
    note right of SupportDashboard
        The Support Dashboard provides a real-time
        overview of support operations with key
        metrics, ticket summaries, and quick access
        to common support functions.
    end note
    
    note left of KnowledgeBase
        The Knowledge Base allows administrators
        to create, organize, and manage help articles
        that can be accessed by users and support agents
        to resolve common issues without creating tickets.
    end note
    
    note left of SupportSettings
        Support Settings provides configuration options
        for ticket workflows, SLAs, automation rules,
        and integrations to optimize the support process
        and ensure consistent customer service.
    end note
